gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

God came in Guru's house, Joban's house; 
After that all saints became complete, many householders became yogis.

Here is the translation:

He came to the festival, having been pleased with his mind; 
The colorful ones playfully dance, they have become friends with each other crimson.

Here are the translations:

Nākhē pičkārī bhari rasa, raṁge sakhā kīdhā rasabas;
Sakhā shōbe chhe sundar raṁge, ramē alabelo uchharaṁge.

Haye paherya che hemanahaar, sobhe fulni maala aapar;
Karyaan tilak kesara tanan, teney sobhe chhe sundar gan.

Note: The numbers at the end of the original text are likely page numbers or section markers, and have been omitted in my response.

Here is the translation:

Where drums beat and bugles sound, refuge is found in steady rhythm;
The colorful stage is very much set, as I see immortals mount the sky.
